			<p rend="align(right)"><placeName>Phila.</placeName> <date>June 4 1844</date>&#8211;</p>
			<p><addressee>Mr Leeser</addressee>&#44;</p>
		  <p rend="indent(1)">Dr. Sir</p>
		  <p rend="indent(2)"><persName>Mr. Sherman</persName> refused<lb/> to let the Hebrew Characters go<lb/> out of his hands unless called<lb/> for in person by you<lb/>  Should it not be asking too<lb/> much of you to obtain for<lb/> me <hi rend="underline">1 letter of each sort</hi><lb/> I should be pleased to offer<lb/> you as a slight remuneration<lb/> for the trouble I have caused you<lb/> a copy of the work when<lb/> completed.&#8211;They shall be<lb/> returned in as good order as<lb/> when received.</p>
		  <p rend="indent(9)">Yours truly</p>
		  <p rend="indent(9)"><persName role="author">Thomas F. Adams</persName></p>

